    {
      "logical_unit_id": "MD12809_lu5",
      "document_id": "MD12809",
      "title": "Withdrawn",
      "text": "Withdrawn\nIn terms of the Preamble to and Section 45 of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (RBI\nAct) and Section 35A of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949, Reserve Bank of India issues\nguidelines / instructions for realising the objectives of Clean Note Policy as part of\ncurrency management. With a view to sustain these efforts and to ensure timely and\naccurate reporting of currency chest transactions, instructions on the subject have been\nissued from time to time.",
