    {
      "logical_unit_id": "MD12809_lu30",
      "document_id": "MD12809",
      "title": "5. Business Continuity Plan",
      "text": "5. Business Continuity Plan\nThe CyM-CC portal has the capability for switching / interchanging the user within a bank\nacross the country (user manual is attached for ready reference) for transaction reporting\nand raising other requests. If a CC is unable to access CyM Portal due to connectivity or\nother technical issues in that particular CC, the Back Office (BO) Administrator of the\nbank can map the user-id of another CC of that bank to the CC having connectivity issues\nfor making transactions. On completion of the transactions the user rights shall be\nrestored to the original CC. This functionality would help CCs in avoiding delayed\nreporting and consequent punitive action. Proper record of such authorisations shall be\nmaintained for audit purposes. CC holding banks are advised to include this aspect in\ntheir CC Business Continuity Plan (BCP).",
      "node_type": "section",
      "level": 3,
      "page_range": [
        4
      ],
      "hierarchy_node_ids": [
